<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.152/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-20T17:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">July 20,
                                        1926—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:28
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>44. Your 25, July 12, 3 p.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs states that
                            his Government is prepared to enter into negotiations for a treaty as
                            proposed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>